<TITLE> 99 BDR men detained until Friday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion has arrested some 100 BDR men countrywide until Friday evening as they were fleeing the bloody mutiny at the BDR headquarters in the capital. Throughout Thursday night and Friday, the RAB picked up 39 personnel of the paramilitary border guards from Savar on the outskirts of Dhaka and Tangail, Bogra and Rajbari districts. The elite force detained a further 60 Thursday. The RAB detained them from buses and other vehicles at checkpoints. Some of them were detained with gold ornaments reportedly looted during the mutiny, the RAB said. The detained personnel have been handed over to police, it said. RAB arrested 22 from a checkpoint on Tangail bypass, Sadar Police Station officer-in-charge Ashraf Hossain said. Of them, two sustained injuries when they tried to escape the arrest and were admitted to Tangail General Hospital. Twelve others were picked up from two checkpoints in Savar in an overnight drive Thursday, some of with several ounces of gold ornaments, a RAB officer said Friday. He said the detainees confessed to looting gold ornaments from the headquarters. They were shown arrested and sent to jail at around noon, Ashulia Police Station OC Rafiqul Islam said. Five personnel were detained at Banani of Bogra district at 5:30am, Sadar Police Station OC Ahsan Habib said. One member was arrested in Goalanda of Rajbari district, RAB's Faridpur camp commander Major Shahriar Iqbal said. The RAB picked up 60 fleeing BDR men before 10pm Thursday, stopping buses and other vehicles at a Savar checkpoint on the Dhaka-Aricha highway. They have been detained at the elite force's Savar camp, said RAB officer Ariful Islam Thursday night. More than one captured personnel said they were escaping the headquarters out of fear that they would be tried for the mutiny despite the prime minister's amnesty. Earlier in the day, police and RAB caught 16 BDR men in plainclothes as they tried to escape over the wall of their headquarters. bdnews24
